summary: Just came back from the tower climb where my mom raced up the tower and there was a group of superheros, I recognized most of...
body:
Just came back from the tower climb where my mom raced up the tower and there was a group of superheros, I recognized most of them. Spiderman, Thor, Iron Man, and Wolverine. But I didn’t recognize the female spider man, I asked who she was supposed to be, apparently it was a new superhero called Silk.

Here’s pictures of the medal the people got for participating.

summary: It’s so fucking difficult to keep up with comics sometimes. I’ve been reading Peter Parker: The Spectacular Spider-Man. It got...
body:
It’s so fucking difficult to keep up with comics sometimes.

I’ve been reading Peter Parker: The Spectacular Spider-Man. It got up to Spider-Geddon, and there hasn’t been any more.

According to Comixology it’s ended.

According to the Marvel website it hasn’t, but nothing else has been published and nothing is planned.

I don’t know what is supposed to come next. But it’s 616 so something should come next.

Did Peter get his nap???

Is Friendly Neighbourhood Spider-Man next?

This happend with Daredevil too. Like, I got to Daredevil Back in Black. That stopped without warning, then I found one that’s out in February, then discovered that’s actually 5 issues of “Man Without Fear” that follows on from Back in Black out in January.

I’M SO FUCKING CONFUSED!

Don’t get in to comics. It’s a complicated mess.
